  "chapter": {
    "number": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "I Take Refuge in You"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "A Shiggaion",
          {
            "noteId": 4285
          },
          "of David, which he sang to the LORD concerning the words of Cush, a Benjamite."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD my God, I take refuge in You;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "save me and deliver me from all my pursuers,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "or they will shred my soul like a lion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and tear me to pieces with no one to rescue me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD my God, if I have done this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if injustice is on my hands,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "if I have rewarded my ally",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4286
          },
          {
            "text": "with evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if I have plundered my foe without cause,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then may my enemy pursue me and overtake me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may he trample me to the ground",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and leave my honor in the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Arise, O LORD, in Your anger;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rise up against the fury of my enemies.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Awake, my God, and ordain judgment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let the assembled peoples gather around You;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "take Your seat over them on high.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD judges the peoples;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "vindicate me, O LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "according to my righteousness and integrity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put an end to the evil of the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but establish the righteous,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "O righteous God who searches hearts and minds.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4287
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My shield is with God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who saves the upright in heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "God is a righteous judge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a God who feels indignation each day.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If one does not repent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "God will sharpen His sword;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has bent and strung His bow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has prepared His deadly weapons;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He ordains His arrows with fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the wicked man travails with evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he conceives trouble and births falsehood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has dug a hole and hollowed it out;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he has fallen into a pit of his own making.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His trouble recoils on himself,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his violence falls on his own head.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will thank the LORD for His righteousness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sing praise to the name of the LORD Most High.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
